\par\pard\plain \ql\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs32\b1\i0\cf6 <$Scr_Ps::0><$Scr_H::2>Title:}{\f0\fs32\b0\i0\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::1> Evan has a new friend \endash  meet Diego.<!$Scr_H::2><!$Scr_Cs::1><!$Scr_Ps::0>}
\par\pard\plain \ql\ltrch\loch \f0\fs18\b0\i0\cf5
\par\pard\plain \tx0\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b1\i0\cf7 <$Scr_Ps::2>Summary:<!$Scr_Ps::2><$Scr_Ps::0>}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\li720\fi360\sa120\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf5 Sarah was called away to deal with a minor emergency. She instructed Katie to get Evan and Guido to help deliver the food from her car to the hungry volunteers. Joining Evan and the crew for lunch was a 14-year-old boy who lived in the area. Of his own volition, he walked on site and started helping with the cleanup. Seeing he was unsupervised, Evan took Diego under his wing, and they worked together throughout the morning. With the workday half over, lunch was served.<!$Scr_Ps::0>}
\par\pard\plain \ql\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs18\b0\i0\cf5 <$Scr_H::2><!$Scr_H::2>}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b1\i0\cf7 <$Scr_Ps::2>Leading Context:<!$Scr_Ps::2><$Scr_Ps::3>}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\li720\fi360\sa120\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf5 In the previous scene, Katie and Sarah went into town to pick up sandwiches, snacks, and drinks for the volunteers and the families impacted by the tornado. That scene ended with them returning to the work site to deliver the food to the hungry volunteers.<!$Scr_Ps::3><$Scr_Ps::0>}
\par\pard\plain \ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b1\i0\cf7 <$Scr_H::2>Setting:<!$Scr_H::2><!$Scr_Ps::0><$Scr_Ps::4>}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\li346\fi14\sb60\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b1\i0\cf8 - Location:}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::1> Farmlands of central Illinois<!$Scr_Cs::1>}
\par\plain {\f2\fs24\b1\i0\cf8 - Description of the Lunch Area:}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::1> <!$Scr_Cs::1><!$Scr_Ps::4><$Scr_Ps::3>}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\li720\fi360\sa120\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf5 The open grassy field, a generous stretch of land belonging to one of the tornado's victims, had been transformed into a lively community gathering spot. Encased by a horizon dotted with trees and the distant echoes of reconstruction, the field blossomed with activity. An expansive outdoor tent stood proudly at its heart, a sentinel against the unpredictable whims of sun and rain. Its bright white canopy gleamed under the high midday sun, casting a cool shade beneath its shelter.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf5 Several sturdy picnic bench tables were arranged in an inviting array, their wooden surfaces adorned with cheerful red-checkered tablecloths that fluttered in the gentle breeze. Volunteers and families mingled around them, their laughter and conversation infusing the air with a sense of camaraderie and hope.<!$Scr_Ps::3><$Scr_Ps::4>}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\li346\fi14\sb60\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b1\i0\cf8 - Time: }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::1>Lunchtime at the volunteer event.<!$Scr_Cs::1><!$Scr_Ps::4><$Scr_Ps::0>}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\li346\fi14\sb60\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b1\i0\cf8 - Weather/Environment: }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::1>Typical partly sunny, chilly fall day in central Illinois.<!$Scr_Cs::1><!$Scr_Ps::0>}
\par\pard\plain \ql\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs18\b0\i0\cf5 <$Scr_H::2><!$Scr_H::2>}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b1\i0\cf7 <$Scr_Ps::2>Characters Present:<!$Scr_Ps::2><$Scr_Ps::4>}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\li346\fi14\sb60\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b1\i0\cf8 - Main Characters: }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::1>Evan, Sarah, Katie, Diego, Guido<!$Scr_Cs::1><!$Scr_Ps::4><$Scr_Ps::0>}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\li346\fi14\sb60\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b1\i0\cf8 - Secondary Characters: }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::1>Volunteers and families<!$Scr_Cs::1><!$Scr_Ps::0>}
